<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 02 at 1:36AM CDT  by NWS Dodge City</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of Ford, southwestern
Hodgeman and east central Gray Counties through 215 AM CDT...
At 135 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Howell, moving northeast at 40 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.
This strong thunderstorm will be near...
Dodge City and Ft. Dodge around 150 AM CDT.
Wright around 155 AM CDT.
Other locations in the path of this storm include Spearville.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...55 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
